latticelm
------------------------------------------
This is a program to learn a word-based language model from a collection of
sentences or lattices. It uses non-parametric Bayesian techniques,
specifically the Pitman-Yor language model, to find a good segmentation.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libfst26-1.8.4-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.4-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libfst-devel-1.8.4-1bl1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.phontron.com/latticelm/

Canonical download:
  https://www.phontron.com/latticelm/download/latticelm-0.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack latticelm-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./latticelm-0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/latticelm-0.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/latticelm-0.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(latticelm)
  /usr/bin/latticelm.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/latticelm.README
  /usr/share/doc/latticelm/README

